Sania Mirza became the first Indian to climb to the top of the WTA doubles ranking after she teamed up with Swiss great Martina Hingis to claim the Family Circle Cup title
The 28-year-old won her third successive doubles title with Hingis
Sania Mirza -LRB- left -RRB- and Martina Hingis celebrate their victory at the Family Circle Cup on Sunday
Mirza 's run of winning 14 successive doubles matches with Hingis will see her leapfrog Italians Sara Errani and Roberta Vinci at the top of the standings
